(1) Any person who, when driving or attempting to drive a motor vehicle on a road , is under the influence of intoxicating liquor or drugs to such an extent as to be incapable of having proper control of such vehicle , shall be guilty of an offence and shall upon conviction be sentenced to either— (a) imprisonment for a period of not less than six months nor more than five years; or (b) imprisonment to be served during a number of consecutive week-ends, not being less than thirty nor more than fifty-two, in this section referred to as week-end imprisonment; and may in addition be sentenced to a fine not exceeding fifteen thousand penalty units.
